  "prompt": "How can I find wps pin on my galaxy S5 connected wifi?",
  "response": "To find the WPS (Wi-Fi Protected Setup) PIN on a Galaxy S5, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the Settings app on your device\n\n2. Tap on \"Wi-Fi\"\n\n3. Tap on the connected Wi-Fi network\n\n4. Select \"Show advanced options\" or \"Modify network\"\n\n5. Look for the WPS PIN option\n\nIf you cannot find the WPS PIN through these steps, you may need to:\n\n1. Check your router's manual or settings\n2. Log into your router's admin interface\n3. Contact your router manufacturer or internet service provider\n\nNote: Not all routers support displaying the WPS PIN, and the exact steps might vary slightly depending on your device's software version.\n\nAlternatively, you can:\n- Check your router's physical interface\n- Look in the router's documentation\n- Contact your router's technical support\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
